It is with tremendous disappointment that we have to announce today the cancellation of the Courage World Tour.
 
“I’m so sorry to disappoint all of you once again. I’m working really hard to build back my strength, but touring can be very difficult even when you’re 100%. It’s not fair to you to keep postponing the shows, and even though it breaks my heart, it’s best that we cancel everything now until I’m really ready to be back on stage again. I want you all to know, I’m not giving up… and I can’t wait to see you again!” – Celine xx…
 
Tickets purchased for the forty-two cancelled dates will be refunded via the original point of sale. For further ticket inquiries or options, ticketholders should reach out to their original point of purchase.
 
More information at the link in bio.
-Team Celine
 
C'est avec un immense regret que nous annonçons l'annulation de la tournée mondiale Courage.
 
« Je suis tellement désolée de vous décevoir encore une fois. Je travaille très fort pour retrouver mes forces, mais les tournées peuvent être exigeantes et difficiles, même quand on est à 100 %. Ce serait injuste envers vous de reporter les concerts une fois de plus, et bien que cela me brise le cœur, il vaut mieux tout annuler maintenant, jusqu'à ce que je sois vraiment prête à remonter sur scène. Je veux que vous sachiez que je n'abandonne pas... et que surtout, j'ai très hâte de vous revoir ! » - Céline xx...
 
Les billets achetés pour les dates annulées seront remboursés au point de vente d'origine. Pour toute question concernant les billets, les détenteurs de billets doivent s'adresser à leur point de vente d'origine.
 
Plus d'information dans le lien en bio.
-Team Céline

After so many years, last night I’m the last man standing - the last resident at @fergusonsdowntown apart from the incredible staff Leon and Hassan who have kept her beautiful for all these years. When I met Tony he told me about his Airstream Village behind the bunkhouse, and @amber3ve and I went down to check it out - behind the Bunkhouse on Fremont Street. But Tony had far greater ambition for his permanent Burning Man community, and built the retail precinct with two restaurants and unique Airstream and mini-house community behind it. Complete with Marley the lama, swimming pool, DJ platform and fire / party every night, it was the perfect community and I easily fell into to staying there when I was doing big projects on the strip. OPM, Atomic, opening Superfrico - heading down to Fergusons to have a @fernetbranca or beer at the end of a massive day, was the perfect place to unwind and escape the strip. We had meetings there, parties there, film premieres there. Harv would come and stay with me and ride his bike around the backlot. I loved it. What Tony created was a fun community. Whether it was beer pong or driving somewhere in his Prevost like turning up to our Christmas party at the Bakery on Fremont Street - he was always organizing something. But now, the community is gone, and I dream of Ferguson being adopted and flying high again with a new visionary who believes in the downtown vision as much as Tony did. I’ve slept my last night, said my goodbyes, and I’m off to found a new community. A circus community - and so tonight I will be in Nipton. The Spiegelworld version of Ferguson. Totally inspired by our friend and artful businessman Tony Hseih. To any of our former residents of Ferguson who would like to drop by - I’ll be having dinner in Nipton around 7pm. Come join us - it will be our big paella pan from Burning Man. And join us as we start the next chapter. And to Tony’s father Richard and his friends and family, I still love East Fremont and can’t wait to start work on our Bakery there. And will be there to cheer on his family as we develop this neighborhood we all love so much.

Pretty pics. Now take your own. A beautiful experience and a team determined to win …. @awakening.wynn @wynnlasvegas …

Repost from @aerosmith
•
To our fans: Unfortunately, Steven’s vocal injury is more serious than initially thought. His doctor has confirmed that in addition to the damage to his vocal cords, he fractured his larynx which requires ongoing care. 
  
He is receiving the best medical treatment available to ensure his recovery is swift, but given the nature of a fracture, he is being told patience is essential.
  
As a result, all the currently scheduled PEACE OUT shows must be postponed to sometime in 2024, with new dates to be announced as soon as we know more.  
 
“I am heartbroken to not be out there with Aerosmith, my brothers and the incredible Black Crowes, rocking with the best fans in the world. I promise we will be back as soon as we can!” - Love, Steven
 
All previously purchased tickets will be honored for the rescheduled dates, and refunds will be available for those unable to attend once those dates are announced. Fans with questions regarding refunds should reach out to their point of purchase.
